  <h2>How Are Video Games Made?</h2>
  <p>
    Video games are some of the most complex and creative things humans make! They combine <strong>programming</strong>, <strong>art</strong>, <strong>music</strong>, and <strong>design</strong> — all working together perfectly.
  </p>

  <h2>The Team Behind a Game</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>👩‍💻 <strong>Programmers</strong> — Write the code that makes the game run: movement, physics, AI enemies, scoring.</li>
    <li>🎨 <strong>Artists</strong> — Design characters, environments, animations, and user interfaces.</li>
    <li>🎵 <strong>Sound Designers</strong> — Create background music, sound effects, and voice acting.</li>
    <li>🕹️ <strong>Game Designers</strong> — Plan the levels, rules, and overall experience of the game.</li>
    <li>🧪 <strong>Testers (QA)</strong> — Play the game over and over to find bugs!</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What is a Game Engine?</h2>
  <p>
    A <strong>game engine</strong> is a special program that makes it easier to build games. Instead of writing everything from scratch, programmers use an engine that already handles things like physics, graphics, and sound. Popular game engines include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>🎮 <strong>Unity</strong> — Used for many mobile games and indie games.</li>
    <li>🏔️ <strong>Unreal Engine</strong> — Used for massive, realistic games like Fortnite.</li>
    <li>🐦 <strong>Godot</strong> — A free, open-source engine great for beginners.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Could YOU Make a Game?</h2>
  <p>Yes! Many kids start with tools like <strong>Scratch</strong> or <strong>Roblox Studio</strong> to create their first simple games. Learning to code is the first step to becoming a game developer!</p>

  <blockquote>
    Minecraft — one of the most popular games ever — was first made by just ONE person: Markus "Notch" Persson. You could be next!
  </blockquote>

